to take a bicycle!!!! no traffic lights, no traffic on the road, no police, no stop signs, no busy streets, and a bike takes you where you need to go in five minutes! You will be surprised! sometimes you can also catch a bus from one point to another in the city, but the buses available get full of passengers and then there are no seats to sit on. other than that, the only tough part in travelling in Libya is that you need to know Libyan Arabic to communicate with traders since Libya has a vast array of tradable goods.
